    <stitle>DOUBLE DIAPHRAGM MGM SPRING BRAKE - REMOVE - REMOVE SPRING BRAKE ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REMOVE SPRING BRAKE ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cage the spring brake completely. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s04020x_X0402001.xml" xrefid="x0402001">CAGING SPRING</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the cotter pin from the yoke pin, knock out the yoke pin, and remove both air lines
                from the assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0402014">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0402014" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0402013.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove Spring Brake Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. MOUNTING STUD NUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. YOKE</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. YOKE PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. COTTER PIN</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. AIR LINE FITTINGS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Be sure the air line from the inlet port is marked "SPRING BRAKE" for later re-installation
                        reference.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a 15/16-inch wrench, loosen hex nuts (Item 1,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0402014">Figure 14</hotlnk>) on mounting studs and cautiously remove the chamber from
                the mounting bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
